User Stories:

User Story 1
As a horror game player 
I want to touch objects that has a percentage chance to jumpscare by interacting with the object/touching the object 
So that I can feel the adrenaline of jumpscare

User Story 2
As a big fan of Halloween
I want to experience the scare and adrenalin of this game,
so that I can have a feel of this holiday the whole year.

User Story 3
As a admant game player there needs to be an end goal to this game.
I want to win a prize for making it through all 10 levels without quitting or pausing.
That way playing this game seems worth it and not just an adrenaline rush.

Acceptance Criteria:

A jumpscare when the user touches an object in the room. 
A chance to add jumpscares in objects.
Jumpscare images can be halloween related (blood, clowns, etc.) last 5 - 10 seconds.
User will pass to next level in increments of 5 if jumpscare object not found in 3 clicks.
Jump scares will intensify( ex level 1- move to level two after interacting with 5 objects, level 2- move to level 3 after
interacting with 10 items, etc.)
The program will choose the jump scare object at random. With error handler if the jumpscare object is not found in 3 clicks to continue until
max incremented clicks have been reached.
On final level user is rewarded with access code that allows sneak peak to upcoming horror games. 
Display Menu before playing 

User Story 4:
As a user, I want a simple user interface where I can choose between different options, like "1", which can start up the horror game
